text:
Here's a recipe for a basic vanilla cake:

1 c. (2 sticks) unsalted butter, at room temp, plus more for pan
3 c. all-purpose flour
1 tbsp. baking powder
1 tsp. kosher salt
1 3/4 c. granulated sugar
4 large eggs
2 tsp. pure vanilla extract
1 1/4 c. whole milk, at room temp
BUTTERCREAM FROSTING

2 c. confectionersâ€™ sugar
1 c. (2 sticks) unsalted butter, at room temp
1/2 tsp kosher salt
1/4 c. heavy cream
1 1/2 tsp. pure vanilla extract

Step 1
Heat oven to 325Â°F. Butter 9- by 13-in. cake pan and line bottom with parchment, leaving overhang on 2 sides; butter parchment.
Step 2
In bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder and salt.
Step 3
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter and granulated sugar on low speed to combine. Increase speed to medium-high; beat until light and fluffy, about 3 min. Reduce speed to medium; add eggs 1 at a time, beating each until incorporated before adding next. Beat in vanilla.
Step 4
Reduce speed to low and add flour mixture in three parts, alternating with milk and beating just until incorporated.
Step 5
Spread batter into prepared pan and bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 min. Let cool in pan 10 min., then use overhangs to remove from pan and let cool completely.

MAKE BUTTERCREAM FROSTING

Step 1
Using electric mixer, beat confectionersâ€™ sugar, butter and salt on low speed until combined, then increase speed to medium and beat until fluffy, about 3 min. With machine running, slowly add cream. Beat until fluffy, about 3 min. Beat in vanilla.
Step 2
Spread frosting over cooled cake and decorate as desired.

Nutritional information (per serving): 
About 640 calories, 35 g fat (21.5 g saturated), 7 g protein, 420 mg sodium, 76 g carbohydrates, 1 g fiber
